How to install Docker Container?
How to install docker container on centos?

First of all follow the official documentation for docker installation on centos here is the official the link :

https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/centos/#installation-methods

If you dont follow then use these commands:
Here is the steps of docker installation on centos

1- Uninstall the old version
sudo yum remove docker \

                 docker-client \

                 docker-client-latest \

                 docker-common \

                 docker-latest \

                 docker-latest-logrotate \

                 docker-logrotate \

                 docker-engine

2- Setup the repository
sudo yum install -y yum-utils
sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo

3- Install Docker Engine
sudo yum install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin

4- Start Docker
sudo systemctl start docker

